# Gaming
#
# Decision: no dedicated Linux gaming stack. Primary gaming (e.g. Valorant)
# is handled via a separate Windows install on a USB-connected SSD, selected
# at the UEFI boot-device level (see docs/architecture.md — Bootloader).
#
# Only Linux-native gaming interest is Minecraft, which requires nothing
# beyond the JDK already declared in development.list (jdk-openjdk).
#
# No Steam / Proton / Lutris installed. Revisit this file only if that
# changes.
